I was lookingforward to that.

01:57.200 --> 01:58.743
(chuckles)

02:03.665 --> 02:06.709
I sure never dreamedthis is how we would spend

02:06.751 --> 02:08.377
our first anniversary.

02:08.419 --> 02:10.922
MAN (over P.A.): First boardingcall for Southern Pacific

02:10.964 --> 02:13.675
train number 37,

02:13.675 --> 02:16.469
service to Los Angeleson track 12.

02:16.511 --> 02:20.431
Southern Pacific train number37, service to Los Angeles.

02:20.473 --> 02:23.101
That's us.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.186
(train whistle blows)

02:27.063 --> 02:29.607
Now, I want youto write me every day.

02:29.649 --> 02:31.025
I want to know everything.

02:31.067 --> 02:32.819
How you feel.What you had for breakfast.

02:32.861 --> 02:34.654
Whether I kept it down.

02:34.696 --> 02:37.365
Yes.

02:39.993 --> 02:41.953
(hissing)

02:55.175 --> 02:57.552
Oh, no, no, no.

02:57.594 --> 03:01.014
Caroline, listen,we'll get through this.

03:01.055 --> 03:02.473
Promise you'll come back.

03:02.515 --> 03:05.977
I'll come back,I'll come back, I promise.

03:11.858 --> 03:14.110
(both laughing)

03:19.908 --> 03:23.453
Last call forSouthern Pacific 37.

03:27.498 --> 03:28.750
(sobbing)It's all right.

03:28.750 --> 03:30.293
It's okay.

03:35.423 --> 03:37.258
I'll wait for you.

03:47.310 --> 03:50.939
(train brakes hissing)

03:50.939 --> 03:53.900
(train engine chugging)

04:05.203 --> 04:06.996
Neil!

04:08.998 --> 04:11.251
Neil!

04:26.724 --> 04:29.269
CAROLINE:Now you have my heart.

04:29.310 --> 04:32.271
Keep it next to yours and bring it safely back to me.

04:32.313 --> 04:36.276
I'll always love you. Caroline.

04:54.836 --> 04:56.504
NEIL:Caroline!

04:56.546 --> 04:58.548
(gasps)

05:15.732 --> 05:17.984
Happy Valentine's Day.

05:39.547 --> 05:41.341
(big band music fades)

05:47.221 --> 05:50.224
There you are, Mrs. Thomas.How you doing today?

05:50.224 --> 05:51.976
Oh, Mr. Williams.

05:52.018 --> 05:54.020
Sit... Sit down.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.064
Don't you look wonderful.

05:56.105 --> 05:58.399
Well, if I do, thatmakes two of us.

05:58.441 --> 06:02.570
I was just saying to myself,it's about time for that

06:02.570 --> 06:04.072
pretty Caroline Thomasto show up.

06:04.072 --> 06:05.740
And there you are,right on schedule.

06:05.782 --> 06:07.742
Wouldn't want to be late.

06:07.784 --> 06:10.912
No, I--I don't suppose you would.

06:10.953 --> 06:14.290
25 years I've been working here,and you haven't been late once.

06:14.332 --> 06:16.584
Nor in the 40 years before that.

06:16.626 --> 06:19.587
I don't know ifI ever told you this,

06:19.629 --> 06:22.298
but back whenI was still teaching,

06:22.340 --> 06:26.177
I always took Valentine's Dayoff to come here.

06:28.137 --> 06:29.764
Can I get you anything?

06:29.764 --> 06:31.140
Uh, water?

06:31.182 --> 06:32.767
Anything?No, no, I... thank you.

06:32.767 --> 06:35.019
I'll just sit here.

06:35.061 --> 06:36.646
I have everything I need.

06:39.857 --> 06:43.611
Well, take care.

06:43.653 --> 06:47.073
MAN (over P.A.):This is your final boarding callfor train 20...

06:47.115 --> 06:49.033
(theme music plays)

06:49.075 --> 06:50.993
(theme music continues)

06:51.035 --> 06:52.703
WOMAN:And we're out.

06:52.745 --> 06:55.123
I've got some new storiesfor us to discuss.

06:55.164 --> 06:56.958
Great. Did you getthat school janitor

06:56.958 --> 06:58.960
who used his savingsto start a scholarship fund?

06:59.001 --> 07:01.170
Uh, Mr. Figueroa does notwant to be interviewed.

07:01.212 --> 07:04.090
But Senator Irving,on the other hand--

07:04.132 --> 07:06.342
being up for reelectionthis year--

07:06.384 --> 07:09.470
was very eager to sharehis thoughts and memories.

07:09.512 --> 07:11.180
His biography and coverage,

07:11.222 --> 07:14.892
his book, more coverage,articles written by him,

07:14.934 --> 07:16.227
articles written about him

07:16.269 --> 07:19.021
and this is heavy on hisvet rehab initiative.

07:19.063 --> 07:21.649
You know, it's notveryAmerican Diary.

07:21.649 --> 07:22.900
Exactly.

07:22.942 --> 07:24.819
And if you getthe right edge,

07:24.819 --> 07:26.320
you get a shotatWorld Profile.

07:26.320 --> 07:29.657
And I'm going with youas your producing partner.

07:29.657 --> 07:31.909
And we will not bestuck in the land

07:31.951 --> 07:34.454
of soft and sappy anymore.

07:34.495 --> 07:37.123
Maybe you need a drinkof water, Julie.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.459
I'll get right on that.

07:43.337 --> 07:45.840
You feeling stuck, Susan?

07:45.882 --> 07:49.093
Not me. I'm good.

07:49.135 --> 07:50.761
So Julie was justpitching Senator Irving.

07:50.803 --> 07:52.597
She said that he'd loveto be interviewed

07:52.638 --> 07:54.849
and he's up for reelection.Human interest.

07:54.891 --> 07:57.310
Senators are human--sometimes interesting.

07:57.351 --> 07:59.687
We're notWorld Profile.

07:59.687 --> 08:01.314
We'reAmerican Diary.

08:01.355 --> 08:03.191
And this is what worksforAmerican Diary.

08:03.232 --> 08:04.609
It's 1944.

08:04.650 --> 08:07.737
A young bride goesto Union Stationon Valentine's Day--

08:07.778 --> 08:09.155
her anniversary, no less--

08:09.197 --> 08:12.325
to send her young Navy pilothusband off to war.

08:12.366 --> 08:14.619
He swears he'll come back,she swears she'll wait.

08:14.660 --> 08:16.787
He goes missing in action.

08:16.829 --> 08:20.333
But 65 years later,she's still living upto her end of the bargain,

08:20.374 --> 08:23.544
by going down to the stationevery Valentine's Day

08:23.586 --> 08:26.464
including this past February,to wait for his train.

08:26.505 --> 08:28.382
And?

08:28.424 --> 08:30.051
That's it.

08:30.051 --> 08:31.969
Well, what elsehas she done?

08:32.010 --> 08:34.764
I mean, has she starteda support group forNavy wives, what?

08:34.804 --> 08:36.724
She goes downto the station.

08:36.724 --> 08:37.725
She waits.

08:37.767 --> 08:39.059
It's a love story.

08:39.059 --> 08:40.519
You know what itreminds me of?

08:40.561 --> 08:41.812
That Japanese dog story.

08:41.854 --> 08:44.273
The one with the Akita who goeslooking for his master

08:44.315 --> 08:45.316
at the train station

08:45.358 --> 08:46.901
ten years after he dies...Susan.

08:46.943 --> 08:48.486
No, it'll be a real tearjerker.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.196
Dogs and old ladies

08:50.238 --> 08:51.697
who wait at train stations

08:51.739 --> 08:53.282
for their deceasedloved ones? Come on.

08:53.324 --> 08:56.577
Lucas Thomas...Susan Allison.

08:56.577 --> 08:57.578
Hi.

08:57.620 --> 08:59.247
I'm the grandson

08:59.288 --> 09:00.915
of the old ladywho waits at

09:00.957 --> 09:02.583
the train stationfor her deceased loved one.

09:02.583 --> 09:03.751
Oh...

09:03.793 --> 09:05.753
Lucas and my nephew Bobby

09:05.795 --> 09:07.505
are old college buddies.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.423
You know, when Bobby toldmy wife that story,

09:09.423 --> 09:12.843
she was desperate to get meto sit you down, Lucas,

09:12.885 --> 09:15.638
and figure out how toget your grandmotheronAmerican Diary.

09:15.680 --> 09:16.931
I can see why the piece

09:16.973 --> 09:18.683
would work for your show,

09:18.724 --> 09:22.103
but I'm just not sure that mygrandmother's the type of person

09:22.103 --> 09:23.479
to pursue something like this.

09:25.731 --> 09:27.400
Thanks for lunch, Craig.

09:27.441 --> 09:28.442
You're very welcome.

09:30.403 --> 09:31.445
Nice meeting you.

09:34.240 --> 09:36.450
Very smooth, Susan.

09:36.492 --> 09:38.369
I'll get the story.

09:49.505 --> 09:51.299
(car door opens, closes)

09:58.472 --> 10:00.224
(knocking on door)

10:04.687 --> 10:08.816
Hello. I'm Susan Allison,fromAmerican Diaryon GNTV.

10:08.816 --> 10:11.861
Hello. I'm sorry, dear, but I'mnot familiar with your program.

10:11.902 --> 10:13.654
Are you Caroline Thomas?

10:13.696 --> 10:15.197
Yes, I am.

10:15.239 --> 10:17.033
Great. Well, we wouldlove to interview you

10:17.074 --> 10:18.534
for our television show.

10:18.576 --> 10:20.703
Me?

10:20.745 --> 10:22.621
I think you havethe wrong person.

10:22.663 --> 10:25.249
Oh, no. I'm pretty surethat it's you.

10:25.291 --> 10:27.335
Oh, well,that's nice, but...

10:27.335 --> 10:28.753
No, thank you.

10:28.794 --> 10:32.298
And, uh, if you'll excuse me,I have a kettle boiling.

10:32.340 --> 10:34.342
Okay, well...

10:37.678 --> 10:39.639
(sighs)

10:43.059 --> 10:44.727
(knocking)

10:46.312 --> 10:47.521
Hi.

10:47.521 --> 10:49.815
Did I say that I wasfromAmerican Diary?

10:49.857 --> 10:52.276
Yes, you mentioned that.(kettle whistling)

10:52.318 --> 10:54.653
But I have no interestin television,

10:54.695 --> 10:56.739
and as you can hear,I'm a bit busy.

10:56.781 --> 10:58.783
I know Lucas.

10:58.824 --> 11:00.368
You're a friend of Lucas?

11:01.827 --> 11:05.581
Well, why didn't yousay that? Come on in.

11:09.710 --> 11:12.254
Make yourself at home.Would you like some tea?

11:12.296 --> 11:14.298
Thank you.

11:15.800 --> 11:17.176
(kettle whistling stops)

11:37.405 --> 11:39.407
What did you say yourname was again, dear?

11:39.407 --> 11:41.534
Um, Susan.Allison.

11:41.575 --> 11:42.451
Ah...

11:42.493 --> 11:45.079
(phone line ringing)

11:45.079 --> 11:46.038
LUCAS (over phone):Hello?

11:46.080 --> 11:48.582
Hello, Lucas?It's Grandma.

11:48.624 --> 11:52.211
You didn't tell me you hada friend coming by today.

11:53.421 --> 11:55.798
Are you coming, too?

11:55.840 --> 11:57.758
What friend?

11:57.800 --> 11:59.427
Uh, Susan Allison?

11:59.427 --> 12:01.721
Something about an interview.

12:01.762 --> 12:02.805
She's there at the house?

12:02.847 --> 12:05.433
Yes, we're having tea.

12:05.433 --> 12:07.601
I'll be right over, Grandma.

12:07.601 --> 12:10.646
Okay, dear.We'll see you soon.

12:11.730 --> 12:14.191
Grandma.

12:14.233 --> 12:15.735
CAROLINE:Hello, dear.

12:15.776 --> 12:16.944
Hey, Grandma.

12:16.944 --> 12:18.946
Ooh, oh, hey!Lucas, hi!

12:18.988 --> 12:21.657
Hello!How are you?

12:21.699 --> 12:24.034
I'm fine. I'm justa little surprised

12:24.076 --> 12:25.453
to see my "friend" here.

12:25.494 --> 12:27.705
You know, I didn't actuallysay that you were my friend.

12:27.746 --> 12:29.331
I just said that I knew you.Hmm.

12:29.373 --> 12:32.960
Wow. This rosebushis beautiful.

12:32.960 --> 12:34.211
Yeah, that bushis dead.

12:37.715 --> 12:39.383
It is not dead.

12:39.425 --> 12:42.428
And it's very special to me.

12:45.306 --> 12:49.143
My husband and I planted ita long time ago.

12:49.143 --> 12:51.228
And when was that?

12:51.270 --> 12:55.274
Uh, Grandma, could you justexcuse us for a moment?

12:55.316 --> 12:57.276
Uh, well, certainly, dear.

12:57.318 --> 12:59.945
Yeah.I'll, uh, I'll get ussome iced tea.

12:59.987 --> 13:01.947
Oh.Sounds great.

13:01.989 --> 13:04.617
There we are.Thank you.

13:07.870 --> 13:09.163
What are youdoing here?

13:09.205 --> 13:11.040
I thought you had no interestin my grandmother.

13:11.081 --> 13:13.459
You know, I think that

13:13.501 --> 13:15.377
I may have given youthe wrong impression.

13:15.419 --> 13:17.505
Really?But...

13:17.505 --> 13:20.382
I'm here now, so...

13:20.424 --> 13:22.843
Five minutes. Please.

13:22.885 --> 13:25.346
(sighs)

13:25.346 --> 13:28.307
We think that it would makethe most beautiful story.

13:28.349 --> 13:30.601
One that would reallyimpact people's lives,

13:30.643 --> 13:33.312
and help themto believe in love.

13:33.354 --> 13:36.148
Kind of like thatJapanese dog story.

13:37.525 --> 13:39.360
Japanese dog story?

13:39.360 --> 13:40.528
Um...

13:40.528 --> 13:43.656
Your story reminds peoplewhat matters most.

13:46.116 --> 13:49.119
What I don't understand is...why me?

13:49.161 --> 13:50.704
There were so many womenwho went through

13:50.746 --> 13:53.165
the same thing I did.My story's no different.

13:53.207 --> 13:55.167
Oh, but it is.

13:55.209 --> 13:56.377
Oh, really?

13:56.377 --> 13:59.755
Please, tell us, whatmakes her story so...

13:59.797 --> 14:01.423
different?

14:04.051 --> 14:06.887
Well, um...

14:06.929 --> 14:10.266
You know, you,you kept the love alive.

14:11.684 --> 14:15.396
I'm sorry, dear. I just don'tthink this is for me.

14:15.396 --> 14:18.899
Lots of womenkept the love alive.

14:18.899 --> 14:21.402
I just kept goingto the station.

14:21.402 --> 14:23.487
JULIE:That is so sad.

14:23.529 --> 14:26.657
To have your whole life revolvearound going to a train station,

14:26.699 --> 14:28.868
waiting for someonewho's never coming back.

14:28.909 --> 14:31.370
Julie, it's nother whole life.

14:31.412 --> 14:33.497
It is one day a year.

14:33.539 --> 14:36.834
Aw. You spend that much timeevery weekend waiting for me

14:36.875 --> 14:38.961
to come back from golf.

14:39.003 --> 14:40.421
Susan spends that much time

14:40.462 --> 14:42.923
every few weeks going to theairport to wait for Andrew.

14:42.965 --> 14:44.717
The difference being,I get off the plane.

14:44.758 --> 14:46.927
SUSAN:Uh, usually.

14:46.969 --> 14:49.388
One time. One timeI didn't make my flight.

14:51.265 --> 14:53.851
(sighs)Well, um...

14:53.893 --> 14:55.185
I'm here now.

14:55.227 --> 14:57.229
Cooking for you, serving you.

14:57.271 --> 14:59.189
Oh, I knew it.

14:59.231 --> 15:00.774
The candles and the flowers.

15:00.774 --> 15:03.861
You're buttering me up forsomething. Okay, let me guess.

15:03.903 --> 15:06.655
You have accepted an eight-monthassignment in Uzbekistan.

15:06.697 --> 15:08.032
(laughs)

15:08.073 --> 15:12.202
A lifetime assignment.

15:25.966 --> 15:30.137
That's an engagement ring.

15:30.137 --> 15:32.348
That's, uh, what I saidthe minute I saw it.

15:32.389 --> 15:35.851
I said, "Now, that'san engagement ring!"

15:44.026 --> 15:46.320
And your answer is...?

15:46.362 --> 15:48.405
You never asked the question.

15:51.408 --> 15:53.410
I never askedthe question?

15:53.452 --> 15:56.163
What do you think I was sayingwhen I gave you the ring,

15:56.163 --> 15:57.623
uh, "Want to go see a movie?"

15:57.665 --> 16:01.126
The appropriate words wouldhave been, "Will you marry me?"

16:01.168 --> 16:03.879
And maybe you could havedone it in private.

16:03.921 --> 16:06.173
I wanted to share the momentwith our friends, our...

16:06.215 --> 16:08.759
our very good friendswho probably haven'tstopped whispering

16:08.801 --> 16:11.512
"Poor Andrew" out there.Okay, so what didyou want me to do?

16:11.553 --> 16:14.515
Just say "yes" for their benefitand then back out later on?

16:17.017 --> 16:19.853
You're saying no?

16:19.895 --> 16:22.314
(sighs) No, I...

16:22.356 --> 16:24.233
I don't know.

16:24.274 --> 16:26.527
I thought we'd talked aboutgetting married one day.Yeah!

16:26.527 --> 16:28.445
We did, as in"If we ever..."Should we just go?

16:28.487 --> 16:30.030
My car keys and jacketare in there.

16:30.030 --> 16:31.573
We're, we're good together,we get along.

16:31.615 --> 16:34.034
How do you even knowif we get along, Andrew?

16:34.076 --> 16:36.161
You're always in Guatemala,or Rwanda,

16:36.203 --> 16:38.122
or the backside of Egypt.It's what I do!

16:38.163 --> 16:42.334
I go to places,and I take pictures.

16:42.376 --> 16:44.586
You want me tochange what I do?

16:44.628 --> 16:46.338
No.

16:51.760 --> 16:53.804
You want to break up?

16:56.390 --> 16:58.809
Andrew, there isa huge difference

16:58.851 --> 17:02.438
between saying no to amarriage proposal immediately

17:02.479 --> 17:04.272
than breaking up.

17:06.316 --> 17:08.109
(clears throat)

17:08.152 --> 17:11.571
I'll, uh, call you.Or you'll call me.

17:11.613 --> 17:13.615
Whatever, I...

17:18.619 --> 17:21.582
Keep the ring,think about it, and

17:21.623 --> 17:23.040
when I getback from Fiji...

17:23.083 --> 17:26.420
Fiji, right.

17:26.462 --> 17:27.755
What?

17:27.796 --> 17:29.506
Nothing.

17:29.548 --> 17:32.968
By the time you get back,you will have forgiven me

17:33.010 --> 17:34.762
for embarrassing youin front of our friends,

17:34.762 --> 17:36.930
and I will notfeel weird anymore

17:36.972 --> 17:38.891
that you put me on the spot,

17:38.932 --> 17:41.435
and everything will just...

17:41.435 --> 17:43.395
go back to normal.

17:49.401 --> 17:51.987
Promise me you'llthink about it?

17:52.029 --> 17:54.406
About us.

17:54.448 --> 17:56.450
I will, I promise.

17:58.577 --> 18:00.370
(sighs)

18:03.040 --> 18:04.958
Hey, good night,you guys.

18:05.000 --> 18:06.543
Oh, okay.Night, buddy.

18:06.585 --> 18:08.462
Good night,Andrew.

18:11.632 --> 18:13.217
(sighs)

18:13.258 --> 18:15.636
That must've been awfulfor you guys, I'm so sorry.

18:15.677 --> 18:17.096
There's just a lotto think about.

18:17.137 --> 18:19.139
Yeah, what is thereto think about?

18:19.139 --> 18:20.933
You guys have knowneach other for years.

18:20.974 --> 18:22.392
He's a great guy.

18:22.434 --> 18:24.019
He's an incredible guy.

18:24.061 --> 18:27.356
Right. So, what moredo you want?

18:29.733 --> 18:31.276
I don't know.

18:33.278 --> 18:36.073
Okay. Okay.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.034
Um... why don't you tell mewhat's really going on?

18:42.037 --> 18:43.914
If you're going to spendyour life with somebody,

18:43.956 --> 18:45.082
don't you wantto feel excited?

18:45.124 --> 18:47.292
(sighs)Thrilled, even?

18:47.334 --> 18:49.837
I mean, isn't theresupposed to be...

18:49.878 --> 18:51.797
(whispers): magic?

18:51.839 --> 18:54.591
Look, I just...I want you to remember

18:54.633 --> 18:56.885
that good guys arereally hard to come by.

18:56.927 --> 18:58.512
Remember that whenI'm out golfing.

18:58.554 --> 19:00.013
Got it.

19:00.013 --> 19:01.682
I'm crossing my fingersfor you two.

19:01.723 --> 19:03.016
Thank you.

19:03.016 --> 19:04.017
You're welcome.

19:04.059 --> 19:06.603
Good night.

19:06.645 --> 19:09.022
I just... oh.

19:09.022 --> 19:10.649
I don't want you toregret this decision

19:10.691 --> 19:13.360
somewhere down theroad, that's it.

19:13.402 --> 19:14.862
Okay?Okay.

19:14.903 --> 19:16.572
Okay. I'll call you tomorrow.

19:20.033 --> 19:22.035
(door closes)

19:38.051 --> 19:40.053
(knocking on door)

19:41.513 --> 19:43.056
(sighs)

19:43.056 --> 19:44.016
Hello?

19:44.057 --> 19:45.726
(cell phone rings)

19:45.767 --> 19:47.102
Ooh. Hello?

19:47.144 --> 19:49.313
JULIE:Hi. Why aren't youin the editing room?

19:49.354 --> 19:51.690
'Cause I'm meetingCaroline Thomas again.

19:51.732 --> 19:54.526
Until I get that interview,she's my new best friend.

19:54.568 --> 19:55.736
Right.

19:55.736 --> 19:57.779
But, uh, who is goingto edit your segment?

19:57.821 --> 19:59.323
We are, we're already behind.

19:59.364 --> 20:00.616
Um, you are.

20:00.657 --> 20:03.493
Because you're brilliant, okay?So just cover for me?

20:03.535 --> 20:05.245
Craig wants this done,like, now.

20:05.245 --> 20:06.455
Listen, I gotta go.

20:09.041 --> 20:11.126
Hey, there.

20:11.168 --> 20:12.753
You don't believe incalling ahead, do you?

20:12.794 --> 20:14.713
Phones can be hung up.

20:14.755 --> 20:16.924
What happens when someonesays "no" to you?

20:16.965 --> 20:18.759
Uh, never really happens.

20:20.177 --> 20:21.470
Oh, you should get out more.

20:21.511 --> 20:23.472
Where is she?

20:23.513 --> 20:26.266
Oh, she's probably gettingready to go and didn't hear you.

20:26.308 --> 20:28.769
Go?She's got a standingdate on Saturdays.

20:28.769 --> 20:31.605
Maybe she'll take you along.

20:31.647 --> 20:33.398
On a date?

20:35.233 --> 20:38.278
She's got a real soft spotfor military men.

20:39.863 --> 20:41.782
Uh, I'll just...

20:41.823 --> 20:43.951
I'll wait here.

20:43.951 --> 20:46.453
CAROLINE:Here's my fisherman.

20:46.453 --> 20:49.748
Oh and, Dave, I knowyou like sports, I know that.

20:49.790 --> 20:52.209
That's a new one.Okay. Thank you.

20:52.250 --> 20:53.585
Hi.

20:53.627 --> 20:54.962
Hello.

20:55.003 --> 20:56.672
Would you likea magazine?

20:56.713 --> 20:57.881
"Vilify the New York Yankees

20:57.923 --> 21:00.300
"all you want, but quite simply,

21:00.342 --> 21:02.469
the Yankees are greatfor baseball."

21:02.511 --> 21:04.304
Says who?

21:04.346 --> 21:05.514
(laughter)

21:05.555 --> 21:07.474
Oh, come on.

21:07.516 --> 21:09.977
Well, that's whatit says, anyway.

21:09.977 --> 21:12.771
"It is precisely their statusas the most hatedIsn't it painful?

21:12.813 --> 21:15.774
franchise in sports history..."Seeing all thesemen who've returned?

21:15.816 --> 21:18.902
Now we're talking."This year, yet again,She gets indignant when people

21:18.944 --> 21:21.196
get it wrong aboutwho's really in pain here."they lead the league

21:21.238 --> 21:22.447
in both spending and revenue."

21:22.489 --> 21:24.324
I don't hate them.

21:24.324 --> 21:26.827
I just wish they wouldn't beatthe teams I like better.

21:26.827 --> 21:29.663
SUSAN:So, you think she's going to let me do the story?

21:29.705 --> 21:31.915
Don't know.

21:31.957 --> 21:33.709
Well, you do havesome influence on her.

21:33.750 --> 21:36.420
Well, I won't use it.

21:36.461 --> 21:39.381
Not even if I can convinceyou it's a good thing?

21:39.423 --> 21:41.383
It's not my decision to make.

21:41.425 --> 21:43.427
I'll supportwhatever she decides.

21:43.468 --> 21:45.470
Fair enough.

21:45.512 --> 21:49.349
You know, I think it'ssweet that you support her.

21:49.391 --> 21:51.268
We support each other.

21:51.309 --> 21:52.769
After she lost my grandfather,

21:52.811 --> 21:54.855
her whole life wastaking care of others.

21:54.896 --> 21:58.525
My father,her students, me,

21:58.567 --> 22:00.235
these men.

22:00.277 --> 22:01.486
She was 20 years old.

22:01.528 --> 22:03.405
I want to take careof her now.

22:05.365 --> 22:08.702
You're a very unusual guy.

22:08.744 --> 22:11.371
I don't think so.

22:11.371 --> 22:12.873
What, you don't help

22:12.873 --> 22:16.043
and supportyour family?

22:16.043 --> 22:19.796
Um, basically my family'sall in Boston.

22:19.838 --> 22:21.548
We're not close, really.

22:21.548 --> 22:24.968
My... my dad dieda few years ago,

22:25.010 --> 22:28.764
and my mom and I don't really--we don't see each other, so...

22:28.805 --> 22:30.557
I'm rambling.

22:30.557 --> 22:32.601
And I'm sorryabout that.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.603
Is your lowerback bothering you?

22:34.644 --> 22:36.063
No, it's fine.

22:36.104 --> 22:38.440
Maybe you should trystretching out your hips.

22:38.482 --> 22:40.650
You might findyour flexors are tight.

22:40.692 --> 22:42.736
And...

22:42.778 --> 22:44.363
you weren't rambling.

22:44.404 --> 22:45.572
We were talking.

22:47.365 --> 22:51.369
Yeah, I think your grandmother'sprobably done now, so...

22:54.581 --> 22:55.707
(chuckles)

22:55.749 --> 22:57.918
So why do you do this?

22:57.959 --> 22:59.753
Honestly?

22:59.795 --> 23:01.380
(sighs)

23:01.421 --> 23:04.257
At first I--

23:04.299 --> 23:07.594
I was hoping I'd find my Neil.

23:07.636 --> 23:11.264
There were so manywounded men.

23:11.264 --> 23:15.018
And I kept telling myselfanything's possible.

23:15.060 --> 23:19.231
And then, it changed for you?

23:20.899 --> 23:24.319
Yeah, I... I guess it did.

23:24.361 --> 23:29.449
It made me feel goodto, you know, to help.

23:29.491 --> 23:31.201
Even now.

23:31.243 --> 23:32.911
I'm from a generation

23:32.953 --> 23:35.372
who honors service.

23:35.413 --> 23:38.750
To our country, to each other.

23:38.792 --> 23:40.752
(sighs)

23:40.794 --> 23:43.839
Maybe that sounds old-fashionedto a lot of people.

23:43.880 --> 23:46.174
I don't know about that.

23:46.216 --> 23:47.759
Doesn't sound old-fashionedto me.

23:47.801 --> 23:49.845
But it does sound

23:49.886 --> 23:51.430
like a Thomas family trait.

23:53.265 --> 23:56.226
I like this one.

23:56.268 --> 23:57.310
(both laughing)

24:02.315 --> 24:04.317
Well, I hate to leavegood company,

24:04.317 --> 24:06.278
but I've got somework to catch up on.

24:06.319 --> 24:07.445
Oh, that's all right, Lucas.

24:07.487 --> 24:09.030
And thank you for today.

24:09.072 --> 24:10.282
No problem, Grandma.

24:10.323 --> 24:12.325
Same time next week.

24:12.325 --> 24:14.786
It was good to seeyou again, Susan.

24:14.828 --> 24:16.955
Yeah, I really enjoyed it.

24:16.997 --> 24:18.373
Me, too.

24:23.003 --> 24:24.504
Oh, here.

24:24.546 --> 24:25.505
Thank you.

24:25.505 --> 24:27.674
So what does...what does Lucas do?

24:27.674 --> 24:29.634
You don't know?

24:29.676 --> 24:31.636
He's a physical therapist.

24:31.678 --> 24:33.722
He's about to be published.

24:33.763 --> 24:35.265
Really?

24:35.307 --> 24:36.850
He wrote an exercise book.

24:38.727 --> 24:40.896
So, this has been lovely.

24:40.937 --> 24:42.189
What's next?

24:42.230 --> 24:43.607
Next?

24:43.648 --> 24:46.026
Uh, do you bring inthe cameras, or...?

24:46.067 --> 24:48.236
You're going to letme do the story!

24:48.278 --> 24:49.863
Oh, thank you!

24:49.905 --> 24:51.615
Sorry.

24:51.656 --> 24:53.325
Okay, um... Wow.

24:53.366 --> 24:55.952
Ultimately, we would justlike to get you on tape

24:55.994 --> 24:57.329
telling your sideof the story

24:57.370 --> 24:59.164
in your own words,but in the meantime...

24:59.206 --> 25:01.917
I don't much believein meantime.

25:01.958 --> 25:04.961
Life happens in real time.

25:05.003 --> 25:07.547
How soon do you want to start?

25:07.589 --> 25:11.468
CAROLINE:I hope it's okay if we dothe interview like this.

25:11.509 --> 25:13.887
I... I'll feel morenatural if I'm busy.

25:13.929 --> 25:15.472
Natural is perfect.

25:15.513 --> 25:16.932
Who could wantmore than natural?

25:16.973 --> 25:18.600
Okay, are you ready to start?

25:18.642 --> 25:21.645
Just in my own words?

25:21.686 --> 25:23.980
However you want to tell it.

25:24.022 --> 25:25.357
All right, uh...

25:25.398 --> 25:28.235
I guess we have to startat the beginning.

25:28.235 --> 25:31.279
Although with Neil and me

25:31.321 --> 25:34.032
it's hard to knowwhere it all began.

25:34.074 --> 25:38.245
Uh... I'd known him forever--since grade school.

25:38.286 --> 25:41.915
About a year before graduation,his family moved away,

25:41.915 --> 25:44.251
and we lost touch.

25:44.292 --> 25:47.003
I didn't seen him againtill '43.

25:47.045 --> 25:50.090
(big band music playing)

25:52.592 --> 25:55.262
By then, of course, the war was on.

25:55.262 --> 25:58.431
We planted victory gardens,

25:58.431 --> 26:01.977
collected scrap metal and rubber for recycling.

26:03.728 --> 26:06.940
Everywhere you looked, there was a reminder.

26:06.940 --> 26:09.192
Everyone seemed to have something to do

26:09.234 --> 26:11.903
behind the scenes for the war effort.

26:11.945 --> 26:13.822
That's because we all had

26:13.863 --> 26:16.283
someone we loved "over there."

26:18.118 --> 26:20.620
Folks put stars in their windows

26:20.662 --> 26:24.332
to show how many family members they had overseas.

26:24.374 --> 26:27.919
Everyone was united, bound together

26:27.961 --> 26:30.338
in a sense of patriotism.

26:30.380 --> 26:33.466
I was doing my part by working for the USO.

26:41.308 --> 26:42.559
Caroline?

26:42.601 --> 26:45.770
Caroline Jensen?

26:45.812 --> 26:47.981
Neil. (stammers)

26:47.981 --> 26:49.607
I-I-I can't believe this.

26:49.649 --> 26:51.651
I...

26:53.486 --> 26:56.656
Jenny, Jenny, look who's here.

26:56.698 --> 26:58.158
You remembermy sister?Yes, yeah.

26:58.199 --> 26:59.451
JENNY:Neil Thomas.

26:59.492 --> 27:01.870
Well, you look better thana man has a right to.

27:01.911 --> 27:02.912
You do, too.

27:03.872 --> 27:05.540
I mean, you both look good...

27:05.582 --> 27:07.709
You both look...

27:07.751 --> 27:09.836
You look real good.

27:12.339 --> 27:15.216
(slow ballad playing)

27:15.258 --> 27:20.638
♪ I don't want to setthe world on fire... ♪

27:20.680 --> 27:21.806
Hey, don't do that.

27:21.848 --> 27:23.350
It's delicious.

27:23.391 --> 27:24.934
Come here.

27:24.976 --> 27:27.854
♪ I just want to start ♪

27:27.896 --> 27:29.981
Good?Mm-hmm.

27:30.023 --> 27:31.775
♪ A flame in your heart... ♪

27:31.816 --> 27:34.944
So you're a pilot?Mm-hmm.

27:34.986 --> 27:36.863
Does that meanyou'll have to...?

27:36.863 --> 27:38.656
Um, I'm stateside for now.

27:38.698 --> 27:40.325
A flight training officer--

27:40.367 --> 27:42.702
I'll be working at the NavalAviation Reserve Base.

27:42.744 --> 27:45.997
So, um...

27:46.039 --> 27:47.707
maybe you won't have to...

27:47.707 --> 27:49.376
you know.Oh...

27:49.417 --> 27:52.212
I... who knows?

27:52.253 --> 27:57.342
♪ No other will do... ♪

27:59.094 --> 28:05.475
♪ I've lost all ambitionfor worldly acclaim ♪

28:05.517 --> 28:10.313
♪ I just want to bethe one you love ♪

28:10.355 --> 28:16.152
♪ And with your admissionthat you feel the same ♪

28:16.194 --> 28:21.950
♪ I'll have reached the goalI'm dreaming of, believe me ♪

28:21.991 --> 28:26.913
♪ I don't want to setthe world on fire... ♪

28:26.913 --> 28:29.582
Oh, she was fit to be tied.

28:29.582 --> 28:31.084
It's true.

28:31.126 --> 28:36.089
(continues on radio):♪ I just want to start ♪

28:36.131 --> 28:43.096
♪ A flame in your heart. ♪

28:43.096 --> 28:45.390
MAN (on radio):And now the Mills Brothers

28:45.432 --> 28:47.809
for all of our sweetheartsout there.Oh.

28:47.851 --> 28:49.227
♪ Stars shiningbright above you ♪

28:49.269 --> 28:50.562
Oh, I love this song.

28:50.603 --> 28:52.355
Don't you?♪ Night breezes seem ♪

28:52.397 --> 28:55.024
♪ To whisper "I love you" ♪Yeah, it... It's good.

28:55.066 --> 28:58.486
♪ Birds singingin the sycamore tree ♪

28:58.528 --> 29:02.115
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

29:02.157 --> 29:07.078
♪ Say "nighty-night"and kiss me... ♪

29:07.120 --> 29:10.790
I was feeling awfully guiltyabout having a safe, cushy job.

29:10.790 --> 29:13.877
But then I saw you.

29:16.796 --> 29:19.299
And all of a sudden, I...

29:19.299 --> 29:23.636
Caroline, this may not bethe best time to say this,

29:23.636 --> 29:26.973
but these days youcan't put things off.

29:28.558 --> 29:31.978
When I think back about whenwe were growing up together,

29:31.978 --> 29:35.565
I-I remember so many things.

29:39.944 --> 29:42.197
But for the life of me...

29:47.118 --> 29:50.747
I can't remember a time whenI... I wasn't in love with you.

30:01.508 --> 30:04.260
I wish you'd say something.

30:07.013 --> 30:08.431
(sighs)

30:12.644 --> 30:15.480
I sure wish you'd kiss me.

30:19.108 --> 30:22.820
♪ Sweet dreams that leaveall worries behind you ♪

30:22.862 --> 30:26.533
♪ But in your dreams,whatever they be... ♪

30:26.574 --> 30:29.494
CAROLINE:It took us all of a week to get engaged...

30:29.536 --> 30:31.371
♪ A little dream of me. ♪

30:31.412 --> 30:33.456
...and another three days to get married.

30:36.876 --> 30:40.129
One thing peoplewere learning from that war

30:40.171 --> 30:43.216
was not to waste any time.

30:43.216 --> 30:46.219
You knew betterthan to let love slip away.

30:46.219 --> 30:49.472
JULIE:Have you talked to Andrew?

30:49.514 --> 30:51.057
SUSAN:Phone tag, mostly.

30:51.057 --> 30:52.934
We talk to eachother's machines.

30:52.976 --> 30:55.186
Oh. You decide anything?

30:55.228 --> 30:56.354
About the ring?

30:56.396 --> 30:58.898
Oh, the ring, the man.

30:58.898 --> 31:00.483
You push me morethan he does.

31:00.525 --> 31:02.485
Of course I push youmore than he does.

31:02.527 --> 31:04.195
I talk to youmore than he does.

31:04.237 --> 31:05.738
Yeah, that's the problem.

31:05.738 --> 31:07.240
Yeah, since when?

31:07.240 --> 31:11.828
I thought you likedhaving your independence.

31:11.869 --> 31:13.413
You've got thisgreat guy.

31:13.454 --> 31:16.749
The two of you jet around theworld doing your own things.

31:16.791 --> 31:19.168
I would kill for that kindof freedom.

31:19.210 --> 31:20.587
Yeah, well...

31:20.628 --> 31:22.130
(panting)

31:22.171 --> 31:24.257
I think I might needmore than that.

31:29.554 --> 31:31.598
LUCAS: I'm going to have youback up in there swinging away,

31:31.639 --> 31:34.309
but we're not goingto do that quite yet.

31:34.350 --> 31:36.352
Here's a cool littleexercise you guys can do.

31:36.394 --> 31:37.937
Turn aroundreal quick here.

31:37.979 --> 31:39.355
All right.

31:39.397 --> 31:41.441
Now, I want you to takethis in your left hand.

31:41.441 --> 31:43.568
Right here-- hold it righthere with your left hand.

31:43.610 --> 31:45.486
And then, we're goingto unclip you here.

31:45.528 --> 31:47.113
Uh, this might hurta little bit, now.

31:47.113 --> 31:48.948
All right, I want you totake the movement

31:48.948 --> 31:50.033
just ever soslightly...

31:50.074 --> 31:51.784
Ooh, you feelthat right there?

31:51.784 --> 31:53.036
Don't go past that.

31:53.077 --> 31:55.288
SUSAN:You were great with that kid out there.

31:55.330 --> 31:56.914
Yeah, he wasbeing scouted,

31:56.956 --> 31:59.292
and then he torehis rotator cuff.

31:59.334 --> 32:00.585
He thought his lifewas over,

32:00.627 --> 32:02.211
'cause he couldn'tpitch anymore.

32:02.253 --> 32:04.923
Oh. You'll get himpitching again?Yeah.

32:04.964 --> 32:06.299
Eventually.

32:06.299 --> 32:07.592
It's a slow, hard recovery.

32:07.634 --> 32:09.886
It takes you off the fast trackof having to win.

32:09.928 --> 32:11.638
So, what about you?

32:11.679 --> 32:13.806
Do you miss the fast track?

32:13.806 --> 32:15.892
What do you mean?

32:15.933 --> 32:17.977
Sorry. I Googled you.

32:18.019 --> 32:19.896
Reporter. Bad habit.

32:19.938 --> 32:21.981
Okay. And what did you find?

32:21.981 --> 32:24.901
Well, Mr. Thomas,I read that you

32:24.942 --> 32:27.028
were a star point guardin college,

32:27.070 --> 32:28.154
and then afteryou graduated,

32:28.154 --> 32:29.989
you became a strength trainerfor the NBA,

32:29.989 --> 32:31.074
and a few yearsafter that,

32:31.115 --> 32:33.701
one day, suddenly,you just resigned.

32:33.743 --> 32:35.703
What happened?

32:35.745 --> 32:37.372
Pretty important jobto just walk away from.

32:39.248 --> 32:42.377
Um, well, uh...

32:42.418 --> 32:45.880
not if you lookat the people who do it.

32:45.922 --> 32:48.007
Um, many of them are divorced.

32:48.007 --> 32:51.010
Their kids barelyknow them.

32:51.052 --> 32:53.012
I just figuredI wanted more

32:53.054 --> 32:54.889
than travelingfrom city to city

32:54.931 --> 32:56.307
with a bunch of guys.

32:56.349 --> 32:57.600
And I... I thought

32:57.642 --> 33:01.771
that my grandmotherwas your subject here.

33:01.813 --> 33:04.649
Yeah. She is.

33:04.691 --> 33:06.150
(chuckles)

33:06.192 --> 33:09.862
And you're hereto talk about her?

33:09.904 --> 33:11.531
My hips.

33:11.531 --> 33:13.783
The flexors.

33:13.825 --> 33:15.785
Oh, um... okay.Yeah.

33:15.827 --> 33:17.954
Well, I've got a couple minutesbefore my next appointment,

33:17.996 --> 33:19.664
if you want me to showyou some stretches.

33:19.706 --> 33:21.457
That would be great.

33:21.499 --> 33:22.875
Okay.

33:22.917 --> 33:24.460
Um, well, uh, kickoff your shoes.

33:24.502 --> 33:27.422
Oh, I don't... I don'ttake my heels off, so...

33:27.463 --> 33:28.673
Okay.

33:28.715 --> 33:30.466
Uh... okay, let's startwith a lunge, then.

33:30.508 --> 33:32.051
Uh, let's goright leg forward.

33:32.093 --> 33:33.553
Okay.And left knee down.

33:33.553 --> 33:35.763
Ooh...Wait, let me... let mehelp you out there.

33:35.805 --> 33:37.223
Okay.Okay. All right.

33:37.265 --> 33:39.350
Now, what I wantyou to do is,

33:39.392 --> 33:40.768
I want you to leanback into me.

33:40.810 --> 33:42.019
(softly)Okay.

33:42.061 --> 33:43.771
Feel that stretch.

33:43.813 --> 33:45.231
You feel it?Ooh! You know what?

33:45.273 --> 33:48.067
That... that is probablymy fiancé.

33:48.067 --> 33:49.610
Yep, that's him. Hello.

33:49.652 --> 33:51.070
Andrew, hey.

33:51.070 --> 33:52.155
Thank you so much.

33:52.196 --> 33:53.364
Yes, uh-huh...(phone ringing)

33:53.406 --> 33:54.824
Oh, well, that's...that's weird.

33:54.866 --> 33:56.242
(laughs) Hello?

33:56.284 --> 33:57.702
Andrew, hi. Thank you.

33:57.744 --> 33:59.120
JULIE: It's Julie.Why are you calling me Andrew?

33:59.162 --> 34:00.538
Really, it's... feels better.

34:00.580 --> 34:02.415
Okay.

34:02.457 --> 34:04.167
(sighs)

34:04.208 --> 34:07.503
CAROLINE:My uncle sold us this house...

34:07.545 --> 34:10.965
for $100 down and $50 a month. ♪ You've got toaccentuate the positive ♪

34:11.007 --> 34:13.801
♪ Eliminate the negative,and latch on... ♪

34:13.842 --> 34:16.637
We couldn't wait to see what we could do with it.

34:16.679 --> 34:20.266
♪ To the affirmative, don't messwith Mr. In-Between ♪

34:20.308 --> 34:24.187
♪ You got to spread joyup to the maximum... ♪

34:24.228 --> 34:26.938
The wood was rotten and termite-ridden.

34:26.981 --> 34:29.442
♪ Have faith ♪

34:29.442 --> 34:31.527
But it was ours.

34:31.569 --> 34:33.029
The first thing we had together.

34:33.070 --> 34:36.199
♪ Liable to walkupon the scene ♪

34:36.239 --> 34:39.284
I wouldn't have taken back one glorious moment

34:39.327 --> 34:42.246
of bringing this house to life with my Neil.

34:42.288 --> 34:45.166
The planks of wood, the nails,

34:45.208 --> 34:47.418
the paint, the seasonal garden,

34:47.460 --> 34:50.129
all touched by his hands.

34:50.170 --> 34:53.299
He's so much a part of this house.

34:53.299 --> 34:57.303
He made me a paradise before he left.

34:57.345 --> 35:00.097
And then, my mother gave mea lot of her old furniture.

35:00.139 --> 35:01.474
That rocker in there?

35:01.474 --> 35:05.228
I was sitting in that rocker when Neil proposed.

