Looks like this letter'sfrom someone

40:03.651 --> 40:05.194
with the same last nameas yours.

40:05.236 --> 40:07.238
(laughs) Thanks.

40:13.202 --> 40:15.955
NEIL:Dearest Caroline, I miss you.

40:15.955 --> 40:18.290
Here's a present for my Navy wife

40:18.332 --> 40:21.293
and a plane I whittled for our little one.

40:23.212 --> 40:25.631
We shipped out of San Francisco

40:25.673 --> 40:28.008
and made it to Pearl Harbor in seven days.

40:28.050 --> 40:29.593
Because we're replacements,

40:29.635 --> 40:32.054
we're awaiting assignments to a carrier.

40:32.096 --> 40:34.014
The fighting right now is in

40:34.056 --> 40:35.141
the Marianas and Caroline Islands,

40:35.182 --> 40:36.934
east of the Philippines.

40:36.976 --> 40:40.312
The Marines are taking one island at a time,

40:40.312 --> 40:42.857
while the Navy is claiming the air and sea.

40:42.898 --> 40:46.152
As for me, I...  I think about you every minute.

40:46.193 --> 40:48.946
I keep your Valentine  in my pocket, next to my heart,

40:48.988 --> 40:52.408
to remind myself that one day this will all be behind us

40:52.449 --> 40:55.452
and we'll be together again.

40:55.494 --> 40:58.998
"Sometimes I forget where I amfor a split second

40:58.998 --> 41:02.376
"and look around,half-expecting to see you,

41:02.418 --> 41:06.130
and there's some ugly sailorlooking back at me."

41:06.172 --> 41:08.549
(chuckling)

41:10.801 --> 41:13.137
The rest is mine.

41:15.222 --> 41:17.558
How I lived for these.

41:17.600 --> 41:23.022
Sometimes I'd go weeks on endwithout hearing a word,

41:23.063 --> 41:25.900
then I'd get several at once.

41:37.036 --> 41:40.289
The mood in the neighborhood always got tentative

41:40.331 --> 41:42.750
when Western Union had to make a delivery.

41:48.380 --> 41:51.717
That's what everyone dreaded the most...

41:51.759 --> 41:53.552
getting a telegram.

41:54.762 --> 41:55.888
Hey, there, kids.

41:55.930 --> 41:57.932
Is your mom in back?

42:07.691 --> 42:09.485
I have a telegram

42:09.527 --> 42:11.487
for you, ma'am.

42:13.489 --> 42:14.365
(sobs)

42:14.406 --> 42:16.450
I'm very sorry, ma'am.

42:27.002 --> 42:30.214
But life went marching on...

42:30.256 --> 42:32.925
sometimes at a gallop.

42:32.967 --> 42:35.386
(gasping)

42:52.111 --> 42:54.238
(baby crying)

43:10.963 --> 43:13.632
REPORTER (over radio):It was announced this morning

43:13.632 --> 43:16.927
that the combined forces of theAllied Pacific Fleet and Army,

43:16.969 --> 43:19.555
under the direction of GeneralDouglas MacArthur,

43:19.597 --> 43:22.016
launched attacks againstJapanese forces

43:22.057 --> 43:24.560
throughoutthe Philippine Islands.

43:24.601 --> 43:27.896
In the largest naval armadain American history,

43:27.938 --> 43:30.649
the Pacific Fleet assembledat dawn and began

43:30.691 --> 43:33.652
to engage the enemy on landand sea.(baby fussing)

43:33.652 --> 43:35.821
The U.S. Fifth Army, supportedby naval and air bombardments...

43:35.863 --> 43:42.786
♪ You'll never knowjust how much I miss you ♪

43:42.828 --> 43:47.166
♪ You'll never knowjust how much I care ♪

43:47.166 --> 43:49.418
See the airplane Daddymade for you?

43:52.212 --> 43:55.215
Daddy's flying in his airplaneright now,

43:55.257 --> 43:58.969
(sniffles)and he's thinking about you.

43:59.011 --> 44:04.183
♪ I still couldn't hidemy love for you ♪

44:04.183 --> 44:07.019
♪ You ought to know ♪

44:07.019 --> 44:08.604
Shh...

44:08.646 --> 44:11.190
♪ Why haven't I told you so ♪

44:11.231 --> 44:18.447
♪ A million or more times? ♪

44:18.489 --> 44:26.455
♪ You went away, and my heartwent with you ♪

44:29.333 --> 44:38.050
♪ I speak your namein my every breath ♪

44:38.050 --> 44:47.017
♪ If there is some other wayto prove that I love you ♪

44:47.059 --> 44:52.856
♪ I swear, I don't know how ♪

44:52.898 --> 44:55.401
♪ You'll never know ♪

44:55.401 --> 45:05.411
♪ If you don't know now. ♪

45:07.246 --> 45:09.665
Mrs. Caroline Thomas?(stifled sob)

45:12.876 --> 45:15.254
(weeping)I'm sorry!

45:19.925 --> 45:21.760
Maybe you want to...

45:21.802 --> 45:23.762
call somebody, ma'am.

45:23.804 --> 45:26.557
You do have someone youcan call, don't you?"The Navy Department regrets

45:26.598 --> 45:29.393
"to inform youthat your husband Neil Thomas

45:29.435 --> 45:31.353
is missing following action..."

45:31.395 --> 45:33.856
(baby fussing nearby)

45:33.897 --> 45:36.024
He's not dead.

45:36.066 --> 45:37.818
I mean, they don't know.

45:37.860 --> 45:38.777
(sniffles)

45:38.819 --> 45:40.362
"Missing" isn't dead.

45:40.404 --> 45:41.697
No.

45:41.739 --> 45:44.533
(baby wailing)

45:44.575 --> 45:46.326
Shh...

45:47.828 --> 45:49.830
(baby crying)

45:51.248 --> 45:53.292
My husband's not dead.

45:58.755 --> 45:59.798
(sniffles)

45:59.840 --> 46:02.217
"Missing's" not dead.

46:15.481 --> 46:21.153
That day,the real waiting began.

46:21.153 --> 46:23.655
I believe I'll go inthe house now.

46:27.910 --> 46:29.828
Caroline,are you okay?

46:29.828 --> 46:33.373
Uh, just a littletired, that's all.

46:35.250 --> 46:36.877
Okay, we'll give hera few minutes.

46:36.919 --> 46:38.754
When she comes back,we can...

46:40.130 --> 46:41.882
Okay.

46:43.217 --> 46:44.927
Call 911!

46:44.968 --> 46:46.303
Caroline!Caroline!

46:51.183 --> 46:53.101
Hey, hey.

46:53.143 --> 46:54.311
Hey, she's in ICU.

46:54.353 --> 46:56.313
They said for youto just go back.

47:00.108 --> 47:02.778
Craig said to let himknow how it goes.

47:02.820 --> 47:05.447
I just hope this isn'tour fault.

47:08.867 --> 47:11.537
WOMAN (over P.A.): Dr. Lewis,call extension 4324.

47:11.537 --> 47:13.330
Dr. Lewis, extension 4324.

47:13.372 --> 47:14.248
You're still here.

47:14.289 --> 47:15.958
Yeah, I was worried.I'm worried.

47:15.999 --> 47:18.210
She had a mild heart attack.

47:18.252 --> 47:20.546
They're just gonna runsome tests and see

47:20.587 --> 47:23.048
how muchdamage was done.I'm so sorry.I feel responsible.

47:23.090 --> 47:25.217
No. No, no, no, don't.Yeah, but if...

47:25.259 --> 47:27.302
if talking about this stirredsomething up for her...

47:27.344 --> 47:28.720
Look, in the past few days

47:28.762 --> 47:30.847
she has been the happiestthat I have ever seen her.

47:30.889 --> 47:34.184
She's gotten to bethat girl in love again.

47:36.895 --> 47:40.232
Here. It got cold.

47:40.274 --> 47:41.400
Thanks.

47:46.280 --> 47:48.907
Well, I hope when I'm 80that I have somebody

47:48.949 --> 47:50.784
like you totake care of me.

47:50.826 --> 47:53.996
Like me? (laughs): No.

47:54.037 --> 47:56.790
She's way strongerthan I am.

47:56.832 --> 47:59.251
I just fill in. I...

47:59.251 --> 48:01.211
(sighs)

48:01.253 --> 48:04.131
I just want to make things rightfor her.

48:06.341 --> 48:09.761
Yeah, I...I knowthat that's what you do.

48:09.761 --> 48:11.430
You know,you mend people.

48:13.599 --> 48:16.435
How are you gonna fix a heartthat's not broken?

48:16.435 --> 48:19.021
She was a girlwhen he went missing.

48:19.062 --> 48:23.275
She never had anyone else.

48:23.317 --> 48:26.612
Just one love, her entire life.

48:29.907 --> 48:31.742
Who even gets that?

48:31.783 --> 48:33.869
The real thing?

48:40.500 --> 48:43.462
(sighs):Hey...

48:45.297 --> 48:47.215
This isn't heartbreak.

48:49.217 --> 48:52.429
She just never gave up on love.

48:56.141 --> 48:58.977
WOMAN (over P.A.):Dr. Davis, report to ICU.

48:59.019 --> 49:01.605
I, uh, should getback in there.

49:01.647 --> 49:04.149
Um...Yeah.

49:04.191 --> 49:06.652
Thanks for waiting.

49:06.693 --> 49:08.362
Sure. Yeah.

49:08.403 --> 49:11.823
Of course. Um, hey,you know, here's, um...

49:11.823 --> 49:12.949
here's my information.

49:12.991 --> 49:16.828
So just, you can call meat home, if she needs...

49:16.870 --> 49:18.914
Okay.anything...

49:18.956 --> 49:20.499
Okay.

49:22.334 --> 49:24.002
CRAIG:It's over.

49:24.044 --> 49:25.629
Well, can't we justput it on hold?

49:25.671 --> 49:28.256
Give her a couple of weeks,and then see how she's doing?

49:28.298 --> 49:30.342
And then what?Rush her back

49:30.384 --> 49:32.344
and push her into havinganother heart attack,

49:32.344 --> 49:34.012
and her family sues us?

49:34.054 --> 49:36.390
Who else can wemove up?

49:38.350 --> 49:40.686
(phone rings)

49:40.727 --> 49:41.937
Hey, it's Susan.

49:41.978 --> 49:44.523
ANDREW:Susan, my fiancée?

49:44.523 --> 49:46.483
Susan, who thought we werenot going

49:46.525 --> 49:49.319
to talk about this untilyou got back.

49:49.361 --> 49:50.946
How's Fiji?

49:50.987 --> 49:52.698
Ah, beautiful, romantic,

49:52.739 --> 49:54.783
lonesome.

49:54.825 --> 49:56.493
I can't wait to see you.

49:56.535 --> 49:58.286
Yeah? So whenare you coming home?

49:58.328 --> 50:00.038
I don't know.I've, uh, met these guys

50:00.038 --> 50:01.289
who builtthis unbelievable boat.

50:01.331 --> 50:03.375
They've asked me to stayfor a while

50:03.375 --> 50:04.835
after the assignment's over.

50:04.876 --> 50:06.420
Maybe, you know,do a little sailing.

50:06.461 --> 50:08.380
I thought you couldn't waitto see me.

50:08.422 --> 50:09.715
I can't!

50:09.756 --> 50:12.759
But, Susan, this isa once-in-a-lifetime thing.

50:12.801 --> 50:15.262
Yeah, okay.

50:15.303 --> 50:18.306
Well, enjoy youronce-in-a-lifetime, and, uh...

50:18.348 --> 50:20.851
try not to get lonesome.

50:20.892 --> 50:21.852
I'll call you soon.

50:21.893 --> 50:23.228
Bye.

50:26.773 --> 50:29.401
(phone rings)

50:29.401 --> 50:30.569
Hello?

50:30.610 --> 50:32.028
LUCAS:Hello, yourself.

50:32.070 --> 50:35.782
Oh, h... hi. Um...

50:35.824 --> 50:37.242
How is she?

50:37.242 --> 50:40.454
She's kind of fragile, but thedoctors think she'll mend.

50:40.495 --> 50:42.122
She asked about you.

50:42.164 --> 50:43.540
She asked about me?

50:43.582 --> 50:45.417
She wanted to seehow you were holding up.

50:45.417 --> 50:47.544
Hey, why don't you answeryour door?

50:47.586 --> 50:50.422
Because there's nobody...

50:50.464 --> 50:52.340
Uh...

50:53.425 --> 50:55.761
Well, you can't sayI didn't call

50:55.802 --> 50:57.262
before I showed up.

50:57.304 --> 50:59.473
Yeah, and you can't saythat I wasn't smiling

50:59.514 --> 51:01.558
when I told youthat you can't stay.

51:01.600 --> 51:03.852
I have homework.

51:03.894 --> 51:06.146
Homework?

51:06.188 --> 51:09.149
Yeah, I'm goingto D.C. tomorrow,

51:09.191 --> 51:11.485
and I have some reading.

51:11.526 --> 51:15.238
Okay. Well, then I guess

51:15.280 --> 51:18.575
I will see you whenyou get back.

51:18.617 --> 51:19.659
Okay.

51:19.701 --> 51:23.205
Uh, hey...

51:23.246 --> 51:24.998
I guess I should tell you

51:25.040 --> 51:27.125
my boss Craig,he doesn't think

51:27.167 --> 51:29.586
that the interview stuff isso good for your grandmother,

51:29.628 --> 51:32.756
so he canceled the project.

51:32.798 --> 51:33.715
Wow.

51:33.757 --> 51:37.135
Um, I... I guess

51:37.177 --> 51:41.306
my-my grandmother will bereally disappointed.

51:43.975 --> 51:49.314
Um, so what areyou gonna do now?

51:49.356 --> 51:53.276
Interview softiesand do-gooders.

51:54.986 --> 51:58.448
I mean...

52:00.075 --> 52:04.287
What are yougonna do... now?

52:04.329 --> 52:08.750
I knew I should not haveopened this door.

52:08.792 --> 52:11.128
You want me to leave?

52:11.169 --> 52:12.587
No.

52:13.922 --> 52:17.801
But I think you have to.

52:17.843 --> 52:19.803
So...

52:26.143 --> 52:27.811
(sighs)

52:29.521 --> 52:32.524
SENATOR: Well, you have to knowwhat you stand for, don't you?

52:32.524 --> 52:36.528
And beyond that, a certaincourage of conviction.

52:36.570 --> 52:37.821
I've been blessed.

52:37.863 --> 52:39.030
And every struggle

52:39.072 --> 52:41.575
along the way has broughtits own rewards.

52:41.616 --> 52:43.285
But, hey, don't make itsound as if I'm through.

52:43.326 --> 52:46.121
I-I still intend to bemaking waves as long as

52:46.163 --> 52:47.205
the voters believe in me.

52:47.247 --> 52:49.875
For many years to come,I'm sure.

52:49.875 --> 52:51.710
That's great, guys.Thank you, Senator.

52:51.710 --> 52:54.129
Thank you for giving meso much of your time.My pleasure. My pleasure.

52:54.170 --> 52:56.631
Please let me know when it'sgoing to air, so I can watch it.

52:56.673 --> 52:58.258
And if there's anythingI can do for you

52:58.300 --> 53:00.385
while you're here in Washington,why, let me know.

53:00.427 --> 53:03.305
Thank you.

53:03.346 --> 53:05.348
You know, actually...

53:11.563 --> 53:14.190
(cell phone ringing)

53:14.232 --> 53:15.192
Hello.

53:15.233 --> 53:16.902
SENATOR:Ms. Allison? Max Irving.

53:16.943 --> 53:18.528
We found that informationfor you.

53:18.570 --> 53:20.155
(chuckles):Wow, that was fast.

53:20.197 --> 53:22.449
My assistant'se-mailing it to you now.

53:22.490 --> 53:24.201
Thank you, Senator, really.

53:24.242 --> 53:25.160
No problem.

53:25.202 --> 53:26.912
Sounds good.Great.

53:26.912 --> 53:28.747
(cell phone ringing)

53:28.788 --> 53:30.248
Hey, what's up?

53:30.248 --> 53:32.334
SUSAN: Hey, you know what?I need you to do me a favor.

53:32.375 --> 53:34.628
Uh, I'm gonnaforward you an e-mail.

53:34.669 --> 53:37.047
I need to know how to contactany living relatives

53:37.088 --> 53:39.758
of a man namedBillings, Jeffrey.

53:39.799 --> 53:41.051
Somewhere around Lubbock, Texas.

53:41.092 --> 53:42.052
(phone beeps)

53:42.093 --> 53:43.428
Ooh, that's Lucas.

53:43.470 --> 53:44.429
I got to go.

53:44.471 --> 53:45.472
Lucas?

53:45.513 --> 53:46.765
(dial tone)

53:46.765 --> 53:47.891
Hey.

53:47.933 --> 53:49.768
LUCAS:Hey.

53:49.768 --> 53:51.144
How's our girl?

53:51.186 --> 53:52.938
She's asleep right now.

53:52.938 --> 53:54.773
She's tougher than she looks.

53:54.814 --> 53:56.983
Sweetie.

53:57.025 --> 53:59.444
Thank you.

53:59.444 --> 54:02.530
And my, uh, my folksare in from New York,

54:02.572 --> 54:05.367
so that'll be a nice surprisefor her when she wakes up.

54:05.408 --> 54:06.660
How's D.C.?

54:06.701 --> 54:08.787
Uh, mission accomplished,actually.

54:08.828 --> 54:10.622
I'm changing my flightand heading to Texas.

54:10.664 --> 54:11.831
Texas?

54:11.873 --> 54:13.792
Do you know what was doneto find your grandfather

54:13.833 --> 54:16.211
after he was declared missing?

54:16.253 --> 54:18.338
Um, everything that couldbe done, I'm pretty sure.

54:18.380 --> 54:21.591
I know that my grandmotherstayed after the Navy for years.

54:21.633 --> 54:24.636
And did you know that there weretwo American survivors

54:24.678 --> 54:26.972
on the last missionthat your grandfather flew?

54:26.972 --> 54:27.931
Just one.

54:27.973 --> 54:29.349
A guy named Roberts.

54:29.391 --> 54:31.351
He's not a survivoranymore, though.

54:31.393 --> 54:34.562
He, uh, he died shortly afterhe came back stateside.

54:34.604 --> 54:36.147
Actually, there was another one.

54:36.147 --> 54:38.316
Guy by the name ofJeff Billings.

54:38.358 --> 54:40.110
The Navy had a reportthat he'd been rescued.

54:40.151 --> 54:41.653
Unfortunately, there wasa little paperwork snafu,

54:41.653 --> 54:44.990
and he was officially classifiedas killed in the line of duty,

54:44.990 --> 54:48.410
until seven years ago, when heactually died of natural causes.

54:48.451 --> 54:49.536
Then the paperwork gotstraightened out.

54:49.577 --> 54:50.996
And I'm guessingthat your grandmother

54:51.037 --> 54:52.330
had stopped looking by then.

54:52.372 --> 54:54.666
Not to mention, it was probablya little late for him

54:54.708 --> 54:56.501
to tell us anythingreally useful.

54:56.543 --> 55:01.506
Well, dead men talkall the time, Lucas.

55:22.652 --> 55:23.778
Hi.

55:23.820 --> 55:25.864
Mr. and Mrs.Billings?

55:25.905 --> 55:27.198
I'm Susan Allison.

55:27.198 --> 55:28.825
I spoke with you last nightfrom D.C.

55:28.867 --> 55:30.243
I'm Anne.

55:30.285 --> 55:31.202
Hi.

55:31.202 --> 55:32.162
And this is Glenn.

55:32.203 --> 55:33.621
How do you do, ma'am?

55:33.663 --> 55:34.956
You're thetelevision lady?

55:34.998 --> 55:36.708
Yeah, that's me.

55:36.708 --> 55:38.001
The television lady.

55:38.043 --> 55:40.336
(chuckles) Can I get yousomething to drink?

55:40.378 --> 55:41.379
SUSAN:I'm fine, really.

55:41.421 --> 55:44.716
Thank you for agreeingto speak to me.

55:46.885 --> 55:48.845
Don't know how muchwe can help you, ma'am.

55:48.887 --> 55:52.390
Um, I grew up listeningto all my daddy's war stories,

55:52.432 --> 55:54.517
and I do remember him talkingabout the lieutenant--

55:54.559 --> 55:55.977
that's who saved his life--

55:56.019 --> 55:58.772
but he never did knowwhat became of him.

55:58.813 --> 56:01.608
Wait a minute.

56:01.649 --> 56:04.319
Lieutenant Thomas savedyour father's life?

56:04.360 --> 56:05.236
Yes, ma'am.

56:05.236 --> 56:08.239
They got shot downover Manila Bay,

56:08.239 --> 56:10.784
and they was bothhit pretty bad.

56:10.825 --> 56:13.369
They parachuted to the ground,hid out in the jungle

56:13.411 --> 56:16.748
on the Bataan Peninsulauntil a local was able to get

56:16.790 --> 56:20.210
my daddy backto the Americans.

56:20.251 --> 56:22.462
Well, if they were ableto help your father,

56:22.504 --> 56:24.547
then how comeLieutenant Thomas...?

56:24.589 --> 56:25.924
They had this little cart.

56:25.924 --> 56:27.967
It was only big enoughto hide one man,

56:28.009 --> 56:31.471
and the lieutenantrefused to go.

56:31.513 --> 56:32.597
He said my daddy was

56:32.639 --> 56:34.432
way worse than he was,and they could just

56:34.474 --> 56:38.269
send somebody back after him.

56:38.311 --> 56:40.605
It's all in the letter.

56:40.647 --> 56:43.441
What letter?

56:43.483 --> 56:45.193
It was the first letter

56:45.235 --> 56:49.280
my daddy wrote back homeafter he got rescued.

56:49.280 --> 56:50.782
Anyway, that...

56:50.782 --> 56:53.618
that was the last timemy daddy saw the lieutenant.

56:53.618 --> 56:56.704
Tried to look him up after thewar, but all he could find out

56:56.746 --> 56:59.499
was that he'd been listedas missing in action.

56:59.541 --> 57:02.418
So Lieutenant Thomasjust stayed there in the jungle?

57:02.460 --> 57:03.545
Well, they'dmet some men.

57:03.586 --> 57:06.881
Tribesmen and a coupleof rebel fighters.

57:06.923 --> 57:09.634
At least he wasn't alone.

57:09.634 --> 57:10.927
Here you go, honey.

57:10.969 --> 57:12.429
My daddy wrote it all down.

57:16.558 --> 57:19.352
And I think my mama kept it inthe Bible,

57:19.394 --> 57:21.896
just to remind herself thateverything's in God's hands.

57:30.071 --> 57:32.073
I think mydaddy would want

57:32.115 --> 57:36.077
the lieutenant's wifeto have that, ma'am.

57:39.289 --> 57:40.415
MAN:Here we go.

57:40.456 --> 57:42.709
(chuckles)Home at last, huh?

57:42.750 --> 57:44.002
Hey, you!

57:44.043 --> 57:45.628
Hey. I heard the hospitallet you go

57:45.670 --> 57:47.714
'cause you were too muchfor them to handle.

57:47.755 --> 57:48.673
(chuckles)

57:48.715 --> 57:50.008
How are you?

57:50.008 --> 57:52.510
Oh, glad to see you,that's how I am.

57:52.552 --> 57:54.846
Welcome back.Soon as you put himdown, we can talk.

57:54.846 --> 57:56.139
Oh.(laughter)

57:56.181 --> 57:58.057
Let me introduce youto my parents.

57:58.099 --> 57:59.350
This ismy mother Maggie.

57:59.392 --> 58:00.894
Hi.That's my father Neil, Jr.This is Susan.

58:00.935 --> 58:02.187
Hi, nice tomeet you.Hi.

58:02.187 --> 58:03.730
I feel as ifwe already know you

58:03.771 --> 58:04.981
just from watching your show.

58:05.023 --> 58:06.107
Oh, I'm gladyou enjoy it.

58:06.149 --> 58:08.902
I have a surprise for you.

58:27.212 --> 58:31.132
Neil, your father savedthis man's life.

58:31.174 --> 58:32.717
He had a chanceto be rescued,

58:32.717 --> 58:35.678
and he put the man's life first.

58:35.720 --> 58:39.849
SUSAN:Jeff Billings never knewwhat became of your husband,

58:39.891 --> 58:42.894
but in that letter,he mentions a tribesman, Morang.

58:42.894 --> 58:44.395
I'm gonnacheck it out.

58:44.437 --> 58:46.731
Do you think it's possibleyou could find him?

58:46.773 --> 58:50.401
Somebody somewhere knowswhat happened in that jungle.

58:50.401 --> 58:51.653
And I'm gonna find out.

58:53.696 --> 58:54.906
I promise.

59:00.161 --> 59:02.038
You promised?It was a bitoptimistic, I admit,

59:02.080 --> 59:03.456
but I still thinkI can do it.

59:03.498 --> 59:05.083
And with your own workbeing so totally irrelevant.

59:05.083 --> 59:06.125
Um, this is my work.

59:06.167 --> 59:07.669
You're the one whoput me on the story.

59:07.710 --> 59:08.962
And I took you off.Remember that part?

59:09.003 --> 59:10.171
Yeah, but I thinkif you and I...No.

59:10.213 --> 59:12.215
Please, justlet me explain.No. No.

59:12.257 --> 59:14.884
(sighs)

59:14.926 --> 59:16.344
Fine.

59:16.386 --> 59:18.263
Then you know what,I'll see you in a week.

59:18.304 --> 59:20.098
It's been three yearssince I've had a vacation,

59:20.139 --> 59:21.432
and I'm feelinga bit run down.

59:21.474 --> 59:22.517
Are you serious?Yep.

59:25.687 --> 59:27.981
Job might not be herewhen you get back.

59:28.022 --> 59:29.774
Okay.

59:29.774 --> 59:31.484
If that's how you feel.

59:36.030 --> 59:38.866
Can you reason with her?

59:41.703 --> 59:45.873
I never side with Craig, butall you have is a man's name.

59:45.915 --> 59:47.625
No. Actually,I have a place.

59:47.625 --> 59:49.127
Bataan Peninsula.

59:49.127 --> 59:50.795
Yeah, but you don'tknow he's from there.

59:50.837 --> 59:51.838
Morang was a native.

59:51.879 --> 59:53.423
The-The letter saysthat he was a native.

59:53.464 --> 59:55.008
So? I'm a nativeof New Jersey.

59:55.049 --> 59:56.134
This is notNew Jersey.

59:56.134 --> 59:58.386
Look, I am not gonnalet Caroline Thomas die

59:58.428 --> 01:00:00.763
without the answersthat she has been looking for.

01:00:00.805 --> 01:00:04.017
Because you're fallingfor her grandson.

01:00:04.058 --> 01:00:06.436
Wow. You know what,I teetered on the brink,

01:00:06.477 --> 01:00:08.646
but Caroline--I care about her.

01:00:08.688 --> 01:00:10.315
Susan, whathappened?

01:00:10.315 --> 01:00:11.316
What happened?!

01:00:11.357 --> 01:00:14.444
Nothing.

01:00:14.485 --> 01:00:16.279
Almost nothing.

01:00:16.321 --> 01:00:17.238
What about Andrew?

01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:18.614
I am working on it, okay?

01:00:18.656 --> 01:00:19.949
And I'm gonnaback away from Lucas.

01:00:19.991 --> 01:00:22.285
Okay, because you seem toreally like this guy...

01:00:22.327 --> 01:00:24.495
Look, can we just talk aboutsomething else, okay?

01:00:24.495 --> 01:00:26.372
I'm backing away from Lucas.

01:00:26.414 --> 01:00:27.457
Look at me.

01:00:27.498 --> 01:00:28.666
Backing.

01:00:28.666 --> 01:00:30.335
No Lucas.

01:00:30.376 --> 01:00:31.377
Got it.

01:00:38.176 --> 01:00:40.219
Hey.

01:00:40.261 --> 01:00:41.679
Hey.

01:00:41.721 --> 01:00:45.099
Brought yousomething.

01:00:45.141 --> 01:00:49.854
This will keep youflexible, healthy

01:00:49.854 --> 01:00:53.358
and hopefully...happy.

01:00:53.399 --> 01:00:54.525
Wow.

01:00:54.567 --> 01:00:55.693
It does all that?

01:00:55.693 --> 01:00:58.488
Well, it will, soon as Iteach you how to use it.

01:00:58.529 --> 01:01:01.240
Well, I-I can't accept it.

01:01:01.282 --> 01:01:04.786
Look, I know how busyyou are with work,

01:01:04.827 --> 01:01:07.163
and now you're runningaround for my grandmother.

01:01:07.205 --> 01:01:09.332
I just, I thought,when does she have time

01:01:09.374 --> 01:01:12.418
to take careof herself?

01:01:12.460 --> 01:01:14.754
I run.

01:01:14.796 --> 01:01:17.173
It also comeswith flowers.

01:01:17.215 --> 01:01:19.759
Just a friendlyreminder

01:01:19.801 --> 01:01:21.886
to take a moment, stop,

01:01:21.928 --> 01:01:25.932
lean forward, with your spineproperly aligned and...

01:01:25.973 --> 01:01:27.100
smell the roses.

01:01:27.141 --> 01:01:30.144
I love roses.

01:01:32.563 --> 01:01:33.731
I can't.

01:01:33.731 --> 01:01:35.191
Why not?

01:01:35.233 --> 01:01:36.734
It's just a gift.

01:01:36.776 --> 01:01:37.902
For all you've done.

01:01:37.902 --> 01:01:42.281
I think maybe we shouldjust keep this friendly.

01:01:45.576 --> 01:01:46.911
Friendly.

01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:47.954
Okay.

01:01:47.995 --> 01:01:50.248
Friendly, it is.

01:01:59.257 --> 01:02:01.384
I like you.

01:02:08.516 --> 01:02:11.436
But I am involvedwith someone else.

01:02:11.436 --> 01:02:14.939
And I...

01:02:14.981 --> 01:02:16.774
(sighs)

01:02:16.774 --> 01:02:19.610
...need to decide how Ifeel about him-him first.

01:02:19.610 --> 01:02:20.862
Mm-hmm.

01:02:20.903 --> 01:02:25.116
You had to go and say that,didn't you?

01:02:25.116 --> 01:02:27.076
Now I just like you more.

01:02:30.705 --> 01:02:32.457
(engine starts)

01:02:39.964 --> 01:02:42.008
(water running)

01:02:42.049 --> 01:02:43.676
(water stops)

01:02:49.807 --> 01:02:50.975
(spits)

01:02:54.353 --> 01:02:57.231
SUSAN:Is that as exact as you can get?

01:02:57.273 --> 01:02:59.984
Just "north of Orion Bataan"?

01:02:59.984 --> 01:03:01.986
Okay, well, what aboutthe map coordinates?

01:03:02.028 --> 01:03:05.615
Did the pilot notethe coordinates?

01:03:05.656 --> 01:03:07.366
Uh-huh.

01:03:12.955 --> 01:03:14.248
Didn't I tell you?

01:03:14.290 --> 01:03:16.667
He's becoming a superstararound here.

01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:17.877
You're right, Mom.

01:03:17.919 --> 01:03:19.504
Look at allthis stuff. Wow!

01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:21.547
Oh, I couldn't be more proud.

01:03:21.589 --> 01:03:24.759
I don't know. It's a littleembarrassing, if you ask me.

01:03:24.800 --> 01:03:27.136
Why?

01:03:27.178 --> 01:03:29.305
I just hope that we geta big enough crowd.

01:03:29.347 --> 01:03:31.224
I mean, who's gonna want

01:03:31.265 --> 01:03:33.309
a signed copy ofan exercise book?

01:03:33.351 --> 01:03:35.561
You have helpedso many people.

01:03:35.603 --> 01:03:36.938
They want to meet you.

01:03:36.979 --> 01:03:38.773
MAGGIE:And we'll be here.

01:03:38.815 --> 01:03:41.359
Why not ask Susan?

01:03:41.359 --> 01:03:43.027
Oh, she's cute.

01:03:43.027 --> 01:03:44.654
Okay, you guys, stop,all right?

01:03:44.695 --> 01:03:46.113
She's got a boyfriend.

01:03:46.155 --> 01:03:47.281
It's not gonna happen.

01:03:47.323 --> 01:03:48.241
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:03:48.282 --> 01:03:50.284
It looked like therewas something there.

01:03:50.326 --> 01:03:52.787
No, there'snothing there.

01:03:52.829 --> 01:03:54.747
Oh, I agree with Grandma.

01:03:54.789 --> 01:03:57.375
She looked interestedto me.

01:03:57.416 --> 01:04:00.253
Well, she mentionedsome other guy acouple times now.

01:04:00.294 --> 01:04:01.838
I got the picture.

01:04:01.879 --> 01:04:04.757
Well, don't be soquick to dismiss it.

01:04:04.799 --> 01:04:09.053
You like her, I can tell.

01:04:09.053 --> 01:04:14.058
Maybe this person she talksabout isn't the one.

01:04:19.063 --> 01:04:21.399
(doorbell rings)

01:04:30.741 --> 01:04:32.493
Hey!Hey.

01:04:32.535 --> 01:04:33.911
What are you doing here?!

01:04:33.911 --> 01:04:35.371
I got back a day early.

01:04:35.413 --> 01:04:37.248
Well, I wish that youwould have called me,

01:04:37.290 --> 01:04:39.166
'cause I could'vecome and picked you up.

01:04:39.208 --> 01:04:42.420
Well, if you want,I'll let you driveme back tomorrow.

01:04:42.461 --> 01:04:44.505
So, you're leaving againtomorrow?

01:04:44.547 --> 01:04:47.174
No. No! No, no, no, no!

01:04:47.216 --> 01:04:50.720
Let me, let me start over.I am sorry.

01:04:50.761 --> 01:04:53.764
I've been on a planefor 12 hours,

01:04:53.764 --> 01:04:54.891
and I need a hug.

01:04:54.932 --> 01:04:56.809
Okay.

01:05:01.647 --> 01:05:03.482
Wow.

01:05:03.524 --> 01:05:05.818
Why all the research?

01:05:05.860 --> 01:05:07.570
Is that Bataan?

01:05:07.612 --> 01:05:08.696
What's going on?

01:05:08.738 --> 01:05:10.615
Remember the storythat I told you

01:05:10.656 --> 01:05:12.283
I was doing about the lady

01:05:12.283 --> 01:05:14.285
whose husband she lost inWorld War II?

01:05:14.327 --> 01:05:16.537
Yeah.Well, I'm tryingto help her find him.

01:05:16.579 --> 01:05:17.955
After 60 years?

01:05:17.997 --> 01:05:20.291
Yeah, except now I knowwhere he was

01:05:20.291 --> 01:05:22.668
and the name of the manwho saw him last.

01:05:22.710 --> 01:05:24.295
Morang...Mm-hmm.

01:05:24.337 --> 01:05:26.213
Do you still haveany contacts in

01:05:26.255 --> 01:05:28.549
the Philippines thatmight be able to help?

01:05:28.591 --> 01:05:30.927
Uh, yeah, I still have

01:05:30.968 --> 01:05:32.803
a few contacts there.

01:05:32.845 --> 01:05:35.306
I haven't spoken to themin a while, though.

01:05:35.306 --> 01:05:37.975
You know, it'sthe love of her life,

01:05:38.017 --> 01:05:39.685
and she still has no idea

01:05:39.727 --> 01:05:41.145
what happened to him.

01:05:41.145 --> 01:05:45.149
Well, hey, that's allyou had to say.

01:05:45.149 --> 01:05:47.443
I'll do anything for love.

01:05:49.654 --> 01:05:51.030
I don't want to hurt you.

01:05:52.990 --> 01:05:55.034
Right. No, of course not.

01:05:55.076 --> 01:05:57.912
I'm sorry, Andrew.

01:05:57.954 --> 01:05:59.330
We're just not ready.

01:06:00.665 --> 01:06:01.832
Yeah.

01:06:01.874 --> 01:06:04.126
I was hoping that maybe, uh...

01:06:06.170 --> 01:06:08.965
But I had a feeling.

01:06:09.006 --> 01:06:11.217
We're just not therefor each other.

01:06:11.258 --> 01:06:14.470
And that's not... that'snot your fault, andit's not my fault.

01:06:14.512 --> 01:06:17.556
It just...it is what it is.

01:06:20.017 --> 01:06:22.061
Are you seeing somebody?

01:06:22.103 --> 01:06:24.313
No.

01:06:24.355 --> 01:06:27.650
Why-Why would you...?

01:06:27.692 --> 01:06:32.154
No, I'm... I'm... not.

01:06:40.371 --> 01:06:42.707
(whistles) Um...

01:06:42.748 --> 01:06:46.502
Can you e-mail me

01:06:46.544 --> 01:06:48.879
everything you've found onyour missing soldier?

01:06:48.921 --> 01:06:51.173
Yeah.

01:06:51.215 --> 01:06:52.717
But... what about us?

01:06:52.717 --> 01:06:53.843
Shouldn't we talk about that?

01:06:53.884 --> 01:06:55.386
Not right now.

01:06:55.428 --> 01:06:57.430
I, uh...

01:06:57.471 --> 01:07:01.058
I'm the one who's gotsome thinking to do now.

01:07:10.025 --> 01:07:13.320
ANDREW:I'll call a fewof my contacts over there.

01:07:13.362 --> 01:07:15.740
Maybe one of them knowssomebody who knows somebody.

01:07:15.781 --> 01:07:17.908
It's kind ofa long shot.Thank you...

01:07:17.950 --> 01:07:20.244
for being so incredibly decent.

01:07:33.716 --> 01:07:35.760
IRVING: Well, you have to knowwhat you stand for, don't you?

01:07:35.801 --> 01:07:38.971
And beyond that,it's courage of conviction.

01:07:39.013 --> 01:07:41.640
And in this case...

01:07:41.682 --> 01:07:44.101
(Irving continues indistinctly)

01:08:11.962 --> 01:08:13.798
♪ ♪

01:08:29.229 --> 01:08:32.316
Hello. Would you mindsigning this?

01:08:32.316 --> 01:08:33.651
I can't.

01:08:33.692 --> 01:08:34.819
Why not?

01:08:34.819 --> 01:08:35.944
I didn't write it.

01:08:37.696 --> 01:08:38.906
(chuckles)

01:08:38.948 --> 01:08:40.366
I am so sorry.

01:08:40.407 --> 01:08:42.952
Your grandmother called meand told me to stop by.

01:08:42.993 --> 01:08:44.662
This is really nice for you.

01:08:44.662 --> 01:08:46.412
Congratulations.

01:08:46.455 --> 01:08:48.957
Oh, thanks. Thanks a lot.

01:08:48.999 --> 01:08:53.671
Um, hey, did she tell youthat she's already reading

01:08:53.671 --> 01:08:54.921
to the veterans again?

01:08:54.964 --> 01:08:57.383
I'm so glad thatshe's doing well.

01:08:57.424 --> 01:08:58.509
Yeah.

01:08:58.509 --> 01:09:01.178
Listen, about the lasttime that we talked...

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:03.430
You, you do not need to explain.

01:09:03.471 --> 01:09:05.390
No, actually, I...I feel like I should.

01:09:05.432 --> 01:09:07.225
And I was gonna call you, but...

01:09:07.268 --> 01:09:09.520
I'm-I'm really sorry,but I've got to finish

01:09:09.562 --> 01:09:11.354
this signing here. Um...

01:09:11.397 --> 01:09:13.858
Maybe we can talk another time.

01:09:13.858 --> 01:09:16.152
Sure.

01:09:21.198 --> 01:09:23.450
He's with that nice woman...

01:09:28.788 --> 01:09:30.541
(chuckling)

01:09:39.633 --> 01:09:41.051
You're back.

01:09:41.051 --> 01:09:42.386
Yeah, I'm back.

01:09:42.386 --> 01:09:43.720
What happenedto Mission Impossible?

01:09:43.720 --> 01:09:44.763
Andrew's working on it.

01:09:44.805 --> 01:09:46.223
I'm gonna keep mypromise to Caroline.

01:09:46.265 --> 01:09:48.434
But right now, I havea career to salvage.

01:09:48.475 --> 01:09:49.894
There's something I wassupposed to tell you.

01:09:49.935 --> 01:09:52.395
Hey. Hey!

01:09:52.395 --> 01:09:55.274
I just found outa few minutes ago.(scoffs, stammers)

01:09:55.316 --> 01:09:57.735
What is going onin my office?

01:09:57.776 --> 01:09:59.862
You don't have an office.You quit.

01:09:59.904 --> 01:10:01.447
Uh...

01:10:01.488 --> 01:10:03.699
uh, I did not quit!

01:10:03.741 --> 01:10:05.409
Well, maybe I misunderstood.

01:10:05.409 --> 01:10:07.536
Well, we were hopingyou'd come back,

01:10:07.578 --> 01:10:09.496
so we fixed upa cubicle for you.

01:10:09.538 --> 01:10:11.207
A cubicle?

01:10:13.792 --> 01:10:15.878
Oh, careful.

01:10:15.920 --> 01:10:17.504
(whistle blows)Hut!

